The paper presents a learning-based image registration method using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architecture to predict 3D rigid transformations of arbitrarily oriented 2D image slices. This involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of simulated Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) and fetal brain imagery, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper utilizes a neural network architecture to learn the regression function, which is a common technique in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
